medical_history.chief_complaint: Asymptomatic bradycardia with heart rates of 160 bpm.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient is a 21-month-old female who was referred for evaluation due to asymptomatic bradycardia. Her past medical history indicates fetal bradycardia at 24 weeks of gestation and a small ventricular septal defect that closed by 6 months of age. There have been no symptoms during her first 5 years of life, despite the severe electrocardiographic phenotype observed.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Fetal bradycardia noted at 24 weeks of gestation; small ventricular septal defect which closed spontaneously by 6 months of age.
medical_history.family_history: Family history of premature, unexpected, and unexplained sudden cardiac deaths involving two paternal great aunts.
